JavaScript is a language developed to run client side code of websites inside a browser.
It is dynamically typed and very flexible.

It was the only option to use for client side
code in websites for a long time and still is the most feature complete. 

JavaScript has nothing todo with Java and was named after Java because it was "cool" at the time.

JavaScript is constantly evolving and browsers constantly add more features. 
The last major change of JavaScript was the ECMAScript6 or ECMA2015script.
JavaScript is implemented differently in most browsers but standardized by the Ecma international.

JavaScript is one of the most important languages to know an be able to use well.
